blog.title: ☀️Working day by day for a better life🌴
blog.description:
Being healthier, losing weight the medical way : clean eating, balanced diet, and adapted physical activity. 
🇫🇷 French medical student living and promoting a healthy lifestyle for her and her patients .💉💊
Height : 158cm
Previous weight (January 2018) : 92 kg
Current weight (January 2019) : 75,2 kg 
Let's do this together !💪🥇
Feel free to send me a message if you have any questions concerning my journey or some medical questions regarding weight loss. ✉✏ (in french or english)
Those who are looking for mutual motivation are very welcome 😊
my fitnesspal : newfakeworld
instagram : @claraimmel

summary:
Un an. 
One year.
Tout a commencé avec une remise en cause. Une grosse claque dans la figure. Arriver à son poids maximal ansi...
body:
Un an.

One year.

Tout a commencé avec une remise en cause. Une grosse claque dans la figure. Arriver à son poids maximal ansi qu'une succession d'évènements personnels particuliers.

It all started when I reached my highest weight ever. It was a real shock. Even more considering the events that were happening to me at that time.

Et puis j'ai dit stop. Stop au stress, stop à la dévalorisation. Si je le fais, je le fais bien et pas à moitié comme avant.

And then I took my decision. I said no to that stress that was devouring me, no to my grades that were becoming so bad because of my state of mind, no to self deprecation. I wanted this time to go big and succeed once and for all. I had clearly reached my tipping point.

En tant qu'externe en médecine (5ème année de médecine). J'avais fait un stage en prise en charge des surcharges pondérales. M'occuper de personnes voulant perdre du poids m'a permis de comprendre tout les enjeux médicaux psyco et socio de la chose. J'avais toutes les cartes en main. Il ne manquait que le déclic.

As a 5th year medical student, I was fully aware of all that came in place for a successfull and durable weight loss. I actually did an internship as a future doctor to learn how to help people losing weight and all the medical science and honestly, pure logic around the thing. I had all the tools. I only needed a little push from life.

Ça a débuté en janvier, mais le gros déclic s'est fait en juillet 2018. Et j'ai enfin compris comment il fallait s'y prendre.

It all started in January 2018. But the big change really happened in July 2018. When I finally understood what I needed to do.

J'ai procédé par étapes. J'ai tout d'abord stoppé les mauvaises habitudes, puis les produits transformés (de janvier a juin).

I proceded by steps. It is really important to build habits. So for a few months, I focused of stopping eating between meals. Then when it was achieved, I took a few months and cut the unhealthy processed foods and cooked from scratch all my meals (living in France, it wasn’t really complicated because I already mostly cooked everything with awesome products).

Puis en juillet ce qui a grandement précipité les choses, c'est quand je me suis perdue dans les videos de fitness youtube et que j'ai finalement compris qu'il fallait se mettre à compter les calories.

Then, in July things went WAY FASTER. I binge watched healthy youtube videos and realised that I needed to start counting calories. Simple math, if your intake is bigger than your outake, then you are going to store it. And how does the body stores stuff ? –> FAT!

J'ai téléchargé l'application myfitnesspal.com et j'étais lancée !

I downloaded the app myfitnesspal.com , calculated the amount of calories I should be eating and I was set !

Le sport à toujours été quelque chose que j'aprécie, mais la difficulté à été de se mettre au HIIT 6× par semaine en été avec les cours Lesmills à ma salle de sport tout en étant en déficit calorique.

Sport is a booster. You may lose calories sure, but to lose weight, your food intake counts for 80% of your chances to succeed. I love sports. I went 6 times a week to the gym mostly to do lesmills.com classes because I find it hard to workout alone. It was difficult because of the obvious calorie restriction I was doing. It wasn’t drastic, I was eating what my body needed to be at my goal weight, but I was so used to eating more than it was challenging. Hopefully, I wasn’t working at the hospital and I was able to rest like crazy after my daily workout 🏋️‍♀️

Je n'ai pas encore atteind mon objectif, un IMC dans les normes. Donc une perde d'environ 29kg au total. Mais je m'en suis pas mal rapprochée avec ces 17kg de perdus en 1an !

I did not yet reach my goal which is to lose 29kg. I calculated it based on the healthy BMI I am aiming. But losing 17kg slowly but surely is really unbelieveable and so rewarding !

Finalement c'est devenu une habitude que de gérer tout cet aspect de ma santé et cela m'aide énormément dans mon quotidien d'externe en médecine, d'être résistante au stress et en pleine confiance de mes capacités qu'elles soient physiques ou mentales.

Finally, it has become a habit. I am so much more confident and have better grades even though I study less. I am now better organised , so that I can study medicine, work at the hospital, take care of my family and dog, keep practicing music and go 4 times a week to the gym ! I have never been so confident and proud of myself.

Le début d'année est difficile après les fêtes (j'étais descendue a 73kg), mais je ne perds pas la motivation. Petit à petit je construit mon futur 💪🏆🎉

This begining of 2019 has been difficult because I gained 2 kg after the winter holidays (I’d reach 73kg). But I am not losing any motivation. Little by little, step by step, day by day, I’ll keep my habits and I’ll build new ones along the way 💪🏆🎉

N'hésitez pas à m'ajouter sur my fitnesspal ! Feel free to add me on myfitnesspal ! ( my pseudo : newfakeworld)

The content is mine please do not use my picture without my consent.

J'ai téléchargé l'application myfitnesspal.com et j'étais lancée !

I downloaded the app myfitnesspal.com , calculated the amount of calories I should be eating and I was set !

Le sport à toujours été quelque chose que j'aprécie, mais la difficulté à été de se mettre au HIIT 6× par semaine en été avec les cours Lesmills à ma salle de sport tout en étant en déficit calorique.

Sport is a booster. You may lose calories sure, but to lose weight, your food intake counts for 80% of your chances to succeed. I love sports. I went 6 times a week to the gym mostly to do lesmills.com classes because I find it hard to workout alone. It was difficult because of the obvious calorie restriction I was doing. It wasn’t drastic, I was eating what my body needed to be at my goal weight, but I was so used to eating more than it was challenging. Hopefully, I wasn’t working at the hospital and I was able to rest like crazy after my daily workout 🏋️‍♀️

Je n'ai pas encore atteind mon objectif, un IMC dans les normes. Donc une perde d'environ 29kg au total. Mais je m'en suis pas mal rapprochée avec ces 17kg de perdus en 1an !

I did not yet reach my goal which is to lose 29kg. I calculated it based on the healthy BMI I am aiming. But losing 17kg slowly but surely is really unbelieveable and so rewarding !

Finalement c'est devenu une habitude que de gérer tout cet aspect de ma santé et cela m'aide énormément dans mon quotidien d'externe en médecine, d'être résistante au stress et en pleine confiance de mes capacités qu'elles soient physiques ou mentales.

Finally, it has become a habit. I am so much more confident and have better grades even though I study less. I am now better organised , so that I can study medicine, work at the hospital, take care of my family and dog, keep practicing music and go 4 times a week to the gym ! I have never been so confident and proud of myself.

Le début d'année est difficile après les fêtes (j'étais descendue a 73kg), mais je ne perds pas la motivation. Petit à petit je construit mon futur 💪🏆🎉

This begining of 2019 has been difficult because I gained 2 kg after the winter holidays (I’d reach 73kg). But I am not losing any motivation. Little by little, step by step, day by day, I’ll keep my habits and I’ll build new ones along the way 💪🏆🎉

N'hésitez pas à m'ajouter sur my fitnesspal ! Feel free to add me on myfitnesspal ! ( my pseudo : newfakeworld)
